#)Variable Precedence( Decides which variable value Ansible uses when the same variable is defined in multiple places ):
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*)The below order Ansible follows when the same variable is defined in multiple places.

*)Use Case: To determine which value Ansible will use.

Precedence (Highest to Lowest):
--------------------------------

1. Extra Variables (--extra-vars)
2. Task Variables
3. vars_files
4. vars_prompt
5. Play Variables
6. Inventory Variables


Rule: If the same variable exists in multiple locations, the variable with higher precedence will be used.



###)Difference between Host Variables and Group variables:
----------------------------------------------------------

Host Variables:
---------------

Definition:
Variables that are defined for a specific host in the inventory file are available only to that host.

Use Case:
When different hosts need different values.


# Host Variables assignment format for a specific host in the inventory file

[frontend]
server1 ansible_host=100.53.132.70 NAME=Aaranya COURSE=Ansible
server2 ansible_host=100.53.132.71

Group Variables:
-----------------

Definition:
Variables that are defined for a group in the inventory file are available to all hosts under that group.

Use Case:
When all hosts in that group require the same variables.

# Group Variables assignment format for hosts under a group in the inventory file

[frontend]
100.53.132.71

[frontend:vars]
WIFE=Bujji Megham
HUSBAND=Aaranya



